KANO – Senator Ibrahim Shekarau (Kano central) led G7 on Sunday conveyed a crucial meeting with critical stakeholders across the 44 local government area of the state. The Sunday dialogue came on the heel of possible collapse of talks between the group, and Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje’s faction last week. Mai Mala Buni led Caretaker Committee of the ruling All Progressives Congress had last week set a template for resolving intractable political crises rocking the party in the state. PDP Victory In FCT Council Polls, Good Omen -Ayu How Witches Took Us To Court, Akwa Ibom Governor Recounts Members of Shekarau’s G7 who were buoyed by existing court verdicts felt shortchanged by the intervention and rejected the proposal in its entirety. It was not immediately clear reasons for the meeting, but insider told INDEPENDENT on condition of anonymity that the dialogue is to brief local leaders and foot soldiers on the position of the group. He said “the ongoing meeting is strategic in the sense that it will afford the leadership to brief the people’s representatives at the grass roots on the position of the group”. INDEPENDENT learnt that the leadership of G7 was well represented except Senator Barau Jibrin who was conspicuously absent. Details soon.